question.query: what have been the top projects to raise over the last 30 days

    "text": "![](https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjriemfd/image/upload/v1767995612/veldt/dof53d1xavismcaxhdtl.jpg)

## Top projects to raise (last 30 days)

**1) Rain — $250M Series C (Payments / stablecoin rails)**  
- **$250M** at **$1.95B valuation**  
- Led by **ICONIQ** with participation from **Dragonfly, Galaxy Ventures, Lightspeed**  
- Read: [Crypto Venture Weekly: Jan 5–9, 2026](https://messari.io/report/crypto-venture-weekly-january-5-9-2026)

**2) RedotPay — $107M Series B (Payments / crypto cards)**  
- **$107M** Series B  
- Backers include **Goodwater, Pantera, Circle**  
- Category signal: “crypto neobank + card issuance” getting priced like fintech again

**3) Fuse Energy — $70M Series B (DePIN / energy)**  
- **$70M** Series B  
- Backers include **Balderton, Lowercarbon**  
- DePIN is clearing late-stage rounds at aggressive valuations when there’s real-world deployment

**4) Digital Asset — $50M strategic (Institutional infra / enterprise chain)**  
- **$50M** strategic  
- Backers include **BNY, Nasdaq, S&P Global**  
- This is “regulated rails + incumbents” capital, not narrative capital

**5) LI.FI — $29M Extended Series A (Interop / routing layer)**  
- **$29M** extended Series A  
- Led by **Multicoin** + **CoinFund**  
- Interop is back in favor when it’s framed as **API distribution** rather than bridges

**6) Real Finance — $29M (RWA tokenization)**  
- **$29M** funding led by **Nimbus Capital** (plus others)  
- RWAs continue to fundraise cleanly when they sell **distribution + compliance** (not “tokenize everything”)

![](https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjriemfd/image/upload/v1765576847/veldt/kdzus5kw7rgpdmm0hcfc.jpg)

## Next tier (still meaningful rounds showing where money is flowing)

From the same 30-day window of venture weekly coverage:  
- **Babylon — $15M** private token sale (**Bitcoin staking → lending vaults**)  
- **Surf — $15M** (AI model for crypto markets; **Pantera-led**)  
- **Cascade — $15M** (perps brokerage UX; **Coinbase Ventures/Polychain/Variant/Archetype**)  
- **Crown — $13.5M** (BRL stablecoin issuer; **Paradigm-led**)  
- **AllScale — $5M** (self-custody stablecoin neobank)  
- **Pye Finance — $5M** (Solana stake-account management/trading)

Read: [Crypto Venture Weekly: Dec 8–12, 2025](https://messari.io/report/crypto-venture-weekly-december-8-12-2025)
